Customer Campaign Design|||||||||CR - Customer Campaign Specification|||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||
Name (#SD)|Customer Campaign Design||||||||1|2|3|4|5|6|7||8||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||REF|Identified Semantic APIs
Description|This Service Domain designs and refines customer campaigns (or integrates designs from external campaign specialists). Customer campaigns target the existing customer base and can be proactive (involving customer targeting, contact and solicitation) or self-service and include activities such as cross-sell, up-sell and retention. Version numbering is used to track the impact of changes made to campaigns over their usage.||||||||E|E|E|E|E|E|E||E|||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||Triggering
Example of Use|A retention campaign is updated to provide amended/improved pricing terms that can be offered to targeted customers to help retain their business after a poor response rate has been detected for the campaign|CR Customer Campaign Specification Instance Record|Customer Campaign Specification Instance Record|||||The overall record for a customer campaign design|IO|IO|||IO|IO|IO||O||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||#|Listed Semantic API Descriptions
Executive Summary|Design and refine customer campaign specifications based on their impact|||Customer Campaign Type||||The type or category of customer campaign (e.g. cross-sell, up-sell, retention)|IO|IO||||IO|IO||O||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||1|CrCR Create or register an imported customer campaign design
Key Features|Define the target profile/impact of a campaign Specify a customer campaign Track the impact of a campaign Refine/reconfigure a campaign|||Customer Campaign Description||||A description of the campaign that clarifies the intended context/use of the campaign, the mechanisms employed and the intended/anticipated response/impact|IO|IO||||IO|IO||O||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||2|UpCr Update details of a customer campaign specification or usage record
Functional Pattern|Design|||Customer Campaign Metrics||||Metrics that are defined to assess the target and actual impact of the campaign|IO|IO||||IO|IO||O||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||3|CoCr Control the use of a customer campaign specification (e.g. suspend pending revision)
Asset Type|Customer Campaign||||Customer Campaign Metric Definition|||A description of the metric, defining how it is to be measured in deployment|IO|IO||||IO|IO||O||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||4|EcCR Accept, reject, etc. a customer campaign specification
Generic Artifact|Specification||||Customer Campaign Metric Goal|||A description of the target performance for the metric that can be defined for different usage scenarios as appropriate|IO|IO||||IO|IO||O||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||5|CaCR Capture impact feedback against a customer campaign specification (by version number)
Control Record|Customer Campaign Specification|||Customer Campaign Specification||||The precise make-up of the campaign. Note that all customer campaign specifications are subject to versioning as the campaign is refined over time.|O|IO||||O|O||O||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||6|ExCR Execute an automated action for a customer campaign specification (e.g. confirm eligibility requirements)
Behavior Qualifier Type|Aspects||||Customer Campaign Product/Service Usage|||Details how the campaign aligns with selected products and services, including pricing considerations|O|IO||||O|O||O||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||7|RqCR Request manual intervention with a customer campaign specification (e.g. obtain interpretation guidance)
||||||Customer Campaign Product/Service Type||The type or category of product or service included in the campaign (e.g. current account)|O|IO||||O|O||O||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||8|ReCR Retrieve details about a customer campaign specification (e.g. obtain use and impact reports)
Service Domain Handling||||||Product/Service Campaign Engagement Description||A description of how the product or service is adapted in the context of the campaign (e.g. discounted pricing/preferential rates, waived service fees, gifts or incentives)|O|IO||||O|O||O|||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||
