Executive Summary|Operate the automated facility that provides interactive context sensitive servicing guidance to employees and self-serve customers|BQ Help Selection Instance Record||Help Selection Instance Record||||Specific details for the help text/guidance selection using derived context and iterative user exchanges to narrow in on the required details||||||||||IO||||IO|IO|||O|||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||1|InCR Initialize the interactive help facility
Key Features|Maintain context specific guidance Select and present context specific guidance Refine guidance selection criteria Capture feedback with regard to guidance coverage and usability/quality||||Help Selection Interaction Type|||The type of session provides context for filtering content (e.g. employee, self-service customer)||||||||||IO|||||IO|||O|||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||2|CoCR Control the execution of the interactive help service (e.g. constrain access)
