Prospect Campaign Design|||||||||CR - Prospect Campaign Specification|||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||
Name (#SD)|Prospect Campaign Design||||||||1|2|3|4|5|6|7||8||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||REF|Identified Semantic APIs
Description|This Service Domain designs and refines prospect campaigns (or integrates designs from external campaign specialists). Prospect campaigns target new customer acquisition and are typically proactive (involving prospect targeting, contact and solicitation). Version numbering is used to track the impact of changes made to campaigns over their usage.||||||||E|E|E|E|E|E|E||E|||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||Triggering
Example of Use|A prospect acquisition campaign is updated to provide amended/improved pricing terms that can be offered to targeted prospects poor take-up rate has been detected for the campaign|CR Prospect Campaign Specification Instance Record|Prospect Campaign Specification Instance Record|||||The overall record for a prospect campaign design|IO|IO|||IO|IO|IO||O||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||#|Listed Semantic API Descriptions
Executive Summary|Design and refine prospect campaign specifications based on their impact|||Prospect Campaign Type||||The type or category of prospect campaign (e.g. direct acquisition, product discount incentive)|IO|IO||||IO|IO||O||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||1|CrCR Create or register an imported prospect campaign design
Key Features|Define the target profile/impact of a campaign Specify a prospect campaign Track the impact of a campaign Refine/reconfigure a campaign|||Prospect Campaign Description||||A description of the campaign that clarifies the intended context/use of the campaign, the mechanisms employed and the intended/anticipated response/impact|IO|IO||||IO|IO||O||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||2|UpCr Update details of a prospect campaign specification or usage record
Functional Pattern|Design|||Prospect Campaign Metrics||||Metrics that are defined to assess the target and actual impact of the campaign|IO|IO||||IO|IO||O||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||3|CoCr Control the use of a prospect campaign specification (e.g. suspend pending revision)
Asset Type|Prospect Campaign||||Prospect Campaign Metric Definition|||A description of the metric, defining how it is to be measured in deployment|IO|IO||||IO|IO||O||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||4|EcCR Accept, reject, etc. a prospect campaign specification
Generic Artifact|Specification||||Prospect Campaign Metric Goal|||A description of the target performance for the metric that can be defined for different usage scenarios as appropriate|IO|IO||||IO|IO||O||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||5|CaCR Capture impact feedback against a prospect campaign specification (by version number)
Control Record|Prospect Campaign Specification|||Prospect Campaign Specification||||The precise make-up of the campaign. Note that all prospect campaign specifications are subject to versioning as the campaign is refined over time.|O|IO||||O|O||O||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||6|ExCR Execute an automated action for a prospect campaign specification (e.g. confirm eligibility requirements)
Behavior Qualifier Type|Aspects||||Prospect Campaign Product/Service Usage|||Details how the campaign aligns with selected products and services, including pricing considerations|O|IO||||O|O||O||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||7|RqCR Request manual intervention with a prospect campaign specification (e.g. obtain interpretation guidance)
||||||Prospect Campaign Product/Service Type||The type or category of product or service included in the campaign (e.g. current account)|O|IO||||O|O||O||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||8|ReCR Retrieve details about a prospect campaign specification (e.g. obtain use and impact reports)
